<DOC><DOCNO> AP891118-0129 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-18-89 1844EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-WeatherpageWeather     11-18 0360</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Weatherpage Weather,0369</SECOND><HEAD>Snow In Lower Great Lakes, Cold Grips Midsection</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Snowstorms blanketed the lower Great Lakes on Saturday, droppingup to a foot of snow in northeast Ohio and causing a rash ofaccidents, and unseasonably cold weather chilled the nation's uppermidsection.   Snow showers reached from much of New York state to northwestPennsylvania, Ohio and Michigan. Up to 8 inches of snow wasforecast for northwest New York state. Scattered snow fell onnorthern Maine, as well as southeastern North Dakota and easternSouth Dakota.   In northeast Ohio, travel near Lake Erie was hazardous if notimpossible in some areas, the National Weather Service said.Columbus got only a dusting of snow overnight, but it formed ice onbridges, closing Interstate 70 through downtown.   There was a rash of accidents, including a 15-car pileup onI-70. Near the eastern Ohio town of St. Clairsville, a van carryingmembers of the Muskingum College women's basketball team was hit bya tractor-trailer on the icy interstate, killing two women andinjuring five.   Rain fell in south-central Texas, along the upper Texas coastand in northwest Florida and northwest Oregon.   During the six hours ending at 1 p.m. EST, 2 inches of snow fellat Traverse City, Mich., and 1 inch fell at Sault Ste. Marie, Mich.   Winds gusted to 60 mph at Vedauwoo between Cheyenne and Laramie,Wyo. Wind advisories were posted for the mountains of SouthernCalifornia, as well as areas below major passes and canyons. Ahigh-wind watch was posted through Sunday for the mountains ofWyoming.   Unseasonably low temperatures settled across the UpperMississippi Valley and the Upper Great Lakes.   Low-temperature records for the date were set in Alpena, Mich.,where it was 9 degrees; Burlington, Iowa, 10 degrees; Duluth,Minn., 0; Lamoni, Iowa, 11; Mason City, Iowa; 0; Rochester, Minn.,minus 4; Sioux City, Iowa, 4; Spencer, Iowa, 4; and Waterloo, Iowa,5.   The low temperature for the Lower 48 states Saturday was minus10 at Warroad, Minn.   Temperatures around the nation at 3 p.m. EST ranged from 12degrees at Grand Rapids, Minn., to 80 degrees at Naples, Fla.</TEXT></DOC>